While the exact contribution of the nitro group can vary, in this context we might estimate an increase of about 30°C. This gives us: Base benzene melting point (5.5°C) + 2 methyl groups (5 + 5 = 10°C) + 1 nitro group (30°C) - counteraction (-5°C).
